Xmas2016_storyBookChapt16_copy:
Lester knew there was no point trying to fall asleep tonight. He had one more visitor left to welcome and he was becoming increasingly certain that these visits weren't mere dreams. 
 He waited patiently in his bed for the clock on the wall to strike midnight and his room to fill with light and smoke one last time. 
Soon enough, midnight arrived and from the smoke emerged a much smaller figure than Lester had anticipated. He couldn't be sure, but through the smoke it looked as though the ghost was holding a turtle.
 “Aloha!” said the spirit. 
“Are you the final ghost?&quot;
 “I am here to show you your Christmases yet to come.”
&quot;Are you holding a turtle?&quot;
&quot;Yes, her name is Shelly! I mean... are ready to go on your final journey?&quot;
 “Yes. Let’s just get this over with.”
 “Good. Now, just lay back and close your eyes….”

